Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
When I select 'Female' radio button from Page 01 of Pelvic MRI
And I select any Examination radio button from Page 01 of Pelvic MRI
Then I go to Page 03 and select 'Yes' in Contrast enhanced
And I click on 'Sequences' tab
And I select 'DWI' from the 'Weighting' dropdown
Then I go to Page 06 of Pelvic MRI
And I click on 'Finding' radio button
And dropdown below 'Finding' is enabled

When I select 'Endometriosis' from the dropdown
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And 'Characterization I' tab is preselected

And 'Restricted to serosa' radio button is enabled
And 'Subperitoneal infiltration of > 5 mm' radio button is enabled

And 'Strong' radio button is enabled
And 'Low' radio button is enabled
And 'No' radio button is enabled

And 'Diffusion restriction' checkbox is enabled

And 'Perifocal fat tissue obliteration' checkbox is enabled
And 'Perifocal tightening/shortening' checkbox is enabled

And 'Ureteral stenosis' radio button is enabled
And 'Intestinal stenosis' radio button is enabled
And 'Haematosalpinx' radio button is enabled
And 'Hydrosalpinx' radio button is enabled
And 'Adhesions' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Subperitoneal infiltration of > 5 mm' radio button
Then 'Infiltration muscularis propria' radio button is enabled
And 'Mucosal/wall-crossing infiltration' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Strong' radio button
Then 'Homogeneous' radio button is enabled
And 'Heterogeneous' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Heterogeneous' radio button
Then 'Nodular parts' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Low' radio button
Then 'Homogeneous' radio button is enabled
And 'Heterogeneous' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Heterogeneous' radio button
Then 'Nodular parts' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Ureteral stenosis' radio button
Then 'At the level of the ureterostium' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Intestinal stenosis' radio button
Then 'Prestenotic dilatation' checkbox is enabled
And 'Poststenotic collapse' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Adhesions' radio button
Then 'Posterior displacement of the uterus' checkbox is enabled
And 'Posterior displacement of the ovaries' checkbox is enabled
And 'Cranial displacement of the posterior fornix vaginae' checkbox is enabled
And 'Displacement of intestinal loops' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Posterior displacement of the ovaries' checkbox
Then 'Kissing ovaries' checkbox is enabled

